      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Organizing Your Desk</p>
<p>One of the most important things that a person should keep in mind is to have his desk organized not just once in a while but always. Consider organizing your desk as the main part of your daily job either you work at home or at the office. </p>
<p>What is organizing and how can it get done? </p>
<p>Organizing means having your things arranged in a correct order or placement and it can be done in a lot of different approach depends on the person’s style or liking. Everyone have different preferences, approach, and styles when it comes to arrangement process. </p>
<p>Similar to other arrangement jobs, organizing desks also involve different essential steps to be followed in order to get this task successful and a lot easier. Such steps include:</p>
<p>•	Remove everything from your desk aside from heavy stuff such as computer and printer. </p>
<p>•	Once your desk is cleared-up, have it wiped by a moist, soft, and clean towel then let it dry. </p>
<p>•	Do not forget to pull the drawers, have it wiped and cleaned too and as much as possible remove the junk stuff out of it, keep the stuff which you might need in the future and throw away the trash.</p>
<p>•	Sort through your things by group. Put the same item in one box, bag, or container. </p>
<p>•	Do not forget to have a recycle bin or a garbage bag beside your desk so you can just simply throw your trash inside of it.  </p>
<p>•	Once the cleaning is done, start identifying the location for all your items. For those things that you frequently use, put them in an area which you can easily reach without the need to stand at all.</p>
<p>•	Avoid putting loads of ornaments in your desk such as photos of your kids (One photo would be enough). Place it in the area of your desk which will not cause interruption when you work. </p>
<p>•	Set aside an area for writing purposes. It will make things easier for you as well as make your desk look presentable, neat and organize. </p>
<p>If you wanna learn some more about organizing job, feel free to ask help from professionals, read books, or articles about organizing stuffs, or browse the internet for more references, tips, and suggestions. </p>
<p>I hope the things I mentioned in this article will contribute some help in your job of organizing your desk. Good luck to you! </p>
