      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39890"><span lang="NL">How to maintain and clean hardwood floors.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39890"><span lang="NL"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-34" title="hardwoodfloors2" src="http://www.speedcleaninganswers.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/hardwoodfloors2-225x300.jpg" alt="hardwoodfloors2" width="225" height="300" />Hardwood floors are an asset to any house. They are not cheap in purchase but with proper care they can last a lifetime. Have you ever been to England and visited a stately home or castle? Changes are great they will have a hardwood floor that has been there for centuries with thousands of visitors <span> </span>walking over them.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39890"><span lang="NL">Hardwood floors come in many designs depending on the type of wood that is used. Some floors have to be sanded after installation and then finished with either wax or oil. Others are installed with a ready-to-use top coat. Usually the way to maintain your floor depends on the type of finish that has been used. Some floors can be cleaned using a damp cloth while others can absolutely not handle any water. A special maintenance product suitable for your type of floor is recommended on a regular basis. Your parket seller or installer can tell you what is best for your floor and in most cases they even sell it. For all types of floors daily cleaning, vacuuming your floor is very important to remove dust, sand etc. It is better to prevent these from getting in your house so make sure you have a decent floor mat at every entrance to your house. Fit your furniture, especially those items that glide a lot like chairs with felt covers. Ask your seller or buy at the DYS shop. When you have spilled a liquid never leave it on too long and never use too much water, always absorbing the excessive fluid immediately. <span> </span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39890"><span lang="NL">It goes for all floors that the intensive maintenance will depend on the usage intensity of your floor. If your floor has a wax finish, buff the floor once in a while with paste wax. A lacquered floor can be treated with a polish, after some considerable time when the lacquer has worn the floor will need to be sanded entirely and lacquered again. An oil finish can be reapplied when necessary after using a special cleaner. This way you will be able to enjoy your hardwood floor for many years.</span></p>
