      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39862"><span lang="NL">How can you organize your closet.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39862"><span lang="NL"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-36" title="cleaning-closets" src="http://www.speedcleaninganswers.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/cleaning-closets.jpg" alt="cleaning-closets" width="127" height="86" />Now that winter is almost over and spring will take over most people will want to clean out and reorganize their closet. What to do with your winter clothes which take up so much space. One idea is to buy special bags you can fill and then suck out the air with your vacuum. That way you can store them for instance in a suitcase or in the attic or under your bed. Dust and moths won’t stand a change. </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39862"><span lang="NL">A lot of people’s wardrobes are overfull . Now is a good time to clean out your closet, to throw away the clothes that are worn and give away or sell the clothes you will never wear again. As a rule, if you have not worn something in over a year you will never wear it again. That does not mean that there is not someone else who can still make use of it. Give them to your local charity. Save one or two old t-shirts or pair of trousers for when you might get dirty while working in the garden or doing odd jobs. </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39862"><span lang="NL">T-shirts are best folded three times instead of two times to make smaller stacks. More will fit on the same shelf. </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39862"><span lang="NL">A good store with many items for easy storing is IKEA, for instance they have something you attach in your hanging wardrobe with Velcro and in it you can store shoes or any other items that need storing. It comes in different sizes. They also have a lot of other devices for storing small items such as jewellry, socks, make-up or just knickknackery. They sell special shoe boxes or a multi use-hanger for storing belts, ties, shawls etc. It takes up as little space as a clothes-hanger but it stores up to 28 accessories. You can buy online, check out their website, if only to get ideas or visit one of their shops. Winter boots take up a lot of space in your hallway or closet. You can store them in a suitcase and keep them in the attic till next winter. </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal_68D387F9_011F_1000_ADD2_28F66ACAE16C_39862"><span lang="NL">Decluttering your closet can be a frustrating activity. You will start doing it and not for long you cannot see the wood for the trees. It helps to be aware of that before your begin, do not start if you are pressed for time. The problem is first you will have to take everything out, leaving your room a total mess, before you can put everything properly back again. Some people are natural organizers, they have an eye for perfect organizing. Maybe you can ask someone like that to help you. If you do not know someone like that, I would suggest you take a small section of your wardrobe at a time, for instance first the hanging wardrobe and an other time the the storage section.</span></p>
