      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Do you know how to take care of your mattress?</p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-24" title="mattrass-care" src="http://speedcleaninganswers.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/mattrass-care.jpg" alt="mattrass-care" width="124" height="124" />Sleeping is an important part of our daily routine, without it we will eventually not function properly any more. Besides that, we like spending time in bed, we spend about a third of our live in it. So we want our bed to be comfortable and look nice if possible. But believe it or not, our bed can also make some people ill or what you do not see is just as important.</p>
<p>Did you know that dust mite in your mattress can cause allergic reactions, leading to, among others, asthma, eczema, rhinitis or a stuffy nose in the morning. Our body sheds about a gram of dead skin filled with bacteria every night while producing up to half a litre of sweat. This makes the perfect breeding ground for the on dead skin feeding dust mite who produce a high volume of excrement that causes the diseases.</p>
<p>To begin with, vacuuming your mattress on a regular basis is useful and recommendable though it will not suffice to kill the allergen producing dust mite. Probably the best way to protect your mattress is to buy a mattress protector. These are waterproof, dust mite proof and allergen proof. You can also get these for your pillow and duvet cover, you or your child will be totally protected.</p>
<p>Of course if you do not want to buy these, accidents do happen and sometimes these will make stains on your mattress. You cannot put your mattress in the washing machine, you could try but I think you will be dissapointed so take my word for it. If your mattress gets stained it is important to act immediately, do not let the stain settle in. Use a clean towel or white paper towel to absorb the fluid till it is totally absorbed, then you can use a little bit of detergent for wool to clean the stain. Rinse with clean water, not too much and dry, again with a dry towel till nothing comes out. Work from the edges of the stain to the center. You do not want your mattress to get too wet, it may cause mold or mildew, use your hair-drier if necessary. In any case do not use it while it is still (a little) wet.</p>
<p>What else can you do to keep your mattress in good condition. Flip it every two months, not just from top to bottom but also change the foot and head side. It will help your mattress keep its shape. Air your mattress regularly but never in the sun. Use a mattress cover between your mattress and your actual bed.</p>
