      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>How to remove carpet stains?</p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-18" title="carpet-stains" src="http://speedcleaninganswers.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/carpet-stains.jpg" alt="carpet-stains" width="125" height="100" />The most important factor in removing carpet stains out of your precious carpet or rug is to act immediately. Do not wait foir the stain to settle in or you will be too late. All that is left you then is a professional  carpet stain removal and it may even not work as good as you expect. Not to mention the effect it has on the environment.</p>
<p>Another thing to remember is never rub the stain if you have spilled a liquid. Use an old towel or white paper towel and start blotting the stain, removing the liquid. Repeat this proces with a clean piece of towel till all of the liquid has been removed. After this rinse with clean water and keep blotting the area till it is dry. Always work the stain from the edges till the center and try not to use too much water.</p>
<p>If you have spilled a solid material, like jam or peanut butter, first scrape the substance away with a knife or a spoon before repeating the procedure we described with liquid materials.</p>
<p>There a lot of natural products that can be used when removing stains. How about club soda to remove stains from red wine or vomit, the carbonic acid will dissolve the liquid. You can repeat the procedure mentioned above. But remember do not rub, always blot the area and keep using clean pieces of (paper) towel. When you you have spilled red wine you can also try white wine to remove the stain.</p>
<p>You will not believe the next tip on removing chewing gum stains, peanut butter! I did not either but it works, put it on, leave it there for a few hours and wipe it away.  Another thing you can do is take a piece of ice out of your freezer, rub it over the chewing gum and it will harden so you can remove it easily with the vacuum cleaner. Or dissolve some plain sugar in warm water and rub the chewing gum away.</p>
<p>When you have a blood stain in your carpet try to rinse it with cold water first, or try club soda or milk, let the latter soak for a while.</p>
<p>Spilled coffee on your rug, take a cup of benzine together with a cup of hot water and use it to remove the stain.</p>
<p>Good luck with keeping your carpet or rug as beautiful as it was on the day you bought it. But remember, you have to act fast, do not hesitate.</p>
