      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>How To clean Your Bathroom</p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-21" title="clean-bathroom" src="http://speedcleaninganswers.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/clean-bathroom.jpg" alt="clean-bathroom" width="70" height="91" />The bathroom is the room all members of the family use every day to wash themselves by taking a shower or bath. We also use it to put on make-up or brush our teeth. It can get messy in there and it is very important to keep it clean and hygenic. This is how to clean your bath or shower fast and thorough.</p>
<p>The biggest problems in a bathroom are skin grease and scale. It is important to treat these on a regular basis otherwise the spots they make are there to stay. For everyday cleaning you can use a mild bathroomdetergent, the ones you just spray on and remove with a damp cloth are very easy to use. Use an old tea towel to dry the surfices or mirror. When used on a regular basis they will prevent scale marks on your taps and shower, showerdoor or bath. In case of a severe filthyness it is a good idea to use a special descaling cleaner. Apply it, let it seattle in for a while and then rinse it. Always use plastic gloves when applying because it stings, especially if you have cuts in your hands. It can get on your breath so do not inhale. Maybe it is better to prevent severe scaling, also to protect the environment and your health.</p>
<p>There a lot of natural products very suitable for easy cleaning. You can treat yellow spots caused by dripping taps with lemon juice, rinse with cold water. Oil spots in your bath can be removed by applying toothpaste and rinsing thoroughly. Or use a damp cloth with buttermilk, rinse with warm water. Vinegar is another one, just fill up a plant spray with warm vinegar, let it seattle in for 15 minutes. Then take a damp cloth, put on some more vinegar and wipe the bath or shower cabinet. End by wiping with a dry cloth. You can wrap a damp cloth with vinegar around your taps, leave there for an hour, after removing  just wipe away the dirt.</p>
<p>If you have a dirty shower curtain, wash in the washing machine (40 degrees), use a little bit of detergent and a good dash of bleach. Your shower curtain will last for a few years. When you have to replace your toothbrush do not trow it away, it is perfect to clean the cracks and corners in your bathroom or shower cabinet. Have you ever thought to clean your shower cabinet and at the same time  take a shower? When you have soaped your hair scrub the tiles and the brickwork with green soap, after rinsing your hair rinse the walls. Always drying after you shower will save you a lot of work.</p>
